
= Introduction =

Xhotkeys provides a simple and easily configurable hotkey launcher for the X-Window System, binding keys and mouse buttons to configurable commands. It should work on all desktops (Gnome, KDE, Xfce, ...) available for the UNIX-like operating systems (GNU/Linux, BSD, ...). 

= Install =

{{{
$ sudo python setup.py install
}}}

= Manual configuration =

Example of configuration file: $HOME/.xhotkeysrc:

{{{
[calculator]
    binding = <Control>2
    directory = ~
    command = xcalc

[abiword]
    binding = <Control><Alt>Button3
    directory = ~/docs
    command = abiword
}}}

Allowed modifiers: Control, Alt, Shift, !WinKey, !AltGr
= GUI configuration =

{{{
$ xhotkeys-gui
}}}

= Starting the daemon =

{{{
$ xhotkeysd
}}}

To launch xhotkeysd at startup, configure the sessions of you desktop environment.
